The National Health Service of England has announced that pre-exposure HIV Prevention (PrEP), a pill taken before sex that has been shown to reduce the risk of infection in at-risk individuals by an average of 86 per cent, will now be provided by the health service during the initial three-year trial period of approximately 10,000 people.
She agreed to finance the trial after the Court of Appeal upheld a High Court ruling last year alleging that the National Health Service had the ability to pay for the prep, despite her claims that it should be funded by local authorities.
