Starting in September, people at risk for HIV, thanks to this study conducted in England at the expense of the National Health Service, will have access to a new enabling tool, the use of which a person can control himself without discussing it with a partner, which will lead to the improvement of many, many lives.
We warmly welcome this news. "
Ian Green, president of the Terrence Higgins Foundation, said: "Now first and foremost, care must be taken to ensure that the test is quickly rolled out across the country, and that no one at risk for HIV is forgotten.
