In Russia, there were difficulties in obtaining an international driver's license
Traffic police units are experiencing a shortage of international driving permits (IDPs).
To get such rights, you have to wait a few weeks for the queue, which has become a real problem for holiday-makers who want to go on holiday abroad in their car or rent it there.
It is worth noting that the situation with international driving permits remains contradictory.
The IDP was introduced to make it easier for the foreign police to understand what is written in the National Certificate, as the information is explained in five languages.
The requirements for international rights are enshrined in the 1968 Vienna Convention on Road Traffic, but Russian rights are recognized in countries that have ratified the Vienna Convention.
In reality, however, everything depends on a particular police or rental office: some require an IDP, and some have enough national rights.
In order to be insured, drivers do receive international rights, but it is worth considering that in countries that have not ratified the Convention (e.g. USA, Spain, Mexico, Indonesia), the authorities have the right not to recognize national rights or IDPs.
Now there is a problem with forms in almost all divisions of traffic police, Kommersant reports, having conducted a study in a number of regions.
Thus, in Moscow, the traffic police units simply do not issue talons, the forms have been missing for four months.
You can make an appointment on the public services website, but there the queue has already stretched to mid-August.
In Krasnoyarsk, it is impossible to get an IDP "for technical reasons," without going into details, in Samara region honestly say that there are no forms, a similar situation occurs in other cities.
Many Muscovites have already encountered the problem, and there are more and more such messages in social networks:
Irina Burmistrova: "Guess why you can't get international rights in Moscow?"
Right, because all traffic police departments have run out of forms.
Elena Podkolzina: "Question to people who know!"
We need to get international rights very urgently.
In Moscow all the time is beaten far ahead, there are no vouchers in place at all (there is a button, but the ticket can not give).
It seems that the portal of public services shows that in SPB time free to Fig.
Has anyone tried to get in another city?
Will it work?
According to the Ministry of Internal Affairs of the Russian Federation, the requirements for forms of international driving permits have changed, so new forms are being delivered to the State auto inspection units.
The deficit may be related to this, however, it is not clear what changes are involved, it has not been previously reported.
Forms buys a special purpose Center in the field of road safety (CSN BDD) of the Ministry of Internal Affairs of the Russian Federation and then supplies them to traffic police units.
In recent years, all contracts were signed with "Gozak" JSC: in 2014-2015 almost 200 thousand forms of IDP were produced, in 2016 15 thousand forms were purchased, in 2017-90 thousand, but the last contract was signed on July 18 with "first printing yard" LLC for the manufacture of 70 thousand forms.
There is a version that CSN simply did not manage to hold a tender in time, which caused the deficit.
However, there are other versions of the shortage of forms: because of the crisis, many people began to travel on their own not to Europe, but to cheaper Asian countries - China, Thailand and so on.
It is not clear what rights are being taken there, so people are being reinsured, so there has been an acrimonious demand for international "crusts."
It has recently become known that professional drivers will have to take an examination to confirm their qualifications.
This proposal was made by the Ministry of Transport.
The new International Driving Permit (IDP) has been in force since 31 May 2011.
