On the opposite side is her mitochondrial DNA, a long Caterpillar of pencil-written C, G and A.
By including 200 letters (or nucleotides, as the artist is scientifically exquisitely expressed), Dewey-harborg hoped to show how we are all remarkably similar, at any rate in our biological structure.
