Electricity is cheaper for both residents and producers of Buryat
The decades-long efforts of the Soviet and post-Soviet authorities of the Republic of Buryat (Eastern Siberia) to establish fair tariffs for electricity consumers are beginning to bear fruit.
Since September 1, the cost of low voltage electricity for industrial recipients has been reduced by 25%.
The Federal Antimonopoly Service of the country in accordance with the resolution of the Government of the Russian Federation "on amendments to the rules of the wholesale market of electric energy and power and to the consolidated forecast balance of production and supply of electric energy (capacity) within the framework of the Unified Energy System of Russia according to the subjects of the Russian Federation" (dated July 17, 2017, No. 842) set indicative prices for electricity and power for industrial consumers of the Republic of Buryat.
As a result, the cost of electric energy for Buryat producers is reduced by a quarter, which will make life much easier for small and medium-sized enterprises and individual entrepreneurs.
For many decades, the leaders of the Republic have embraced the thresholds of the Moscow offices in a thorough attempt to align the region in tariffs with the neighboring Irkutsk region with the cascade of hydroelectric power plants on the hangar stemming from Baikal, the main catchment area for which is Buryat.
And it was only this year that advances began.
In March, electricity tariffs for the population of the Republic were reduced from 4.24 rubles / kWh to 3.93 rubles / kWh, or 7.3%.
With the inclusion of Buryat by the decision of the federal government in the list of territories of price zones of the wholesale market, for which the peculiarities of functioning of wholesale and retail markets are established the turn of industrial consumers.
According to analysts, this is only the beginning, as the population of Irkutsk region pays for kilowatt / hour 1.01 rubles.
But no one is daring to give at least an approximate date for new downward tariff moves for Buryat.
