In Russia there will be two new territories of advanced social and economic development - "Abaz" and "Novotroitsk."
The relevant resolutions of the Government of the Russian Federation will come into force today, August 4.
The boundaries and types of economic activity of the Torah in the territory of the City of Abaz in the Republic of Hakasia have been defined.
In the city, where 15 thousand people live, there will be a special legal regime of business, as well as a minimum amount of capital investments of residents, a minimum number of new permanent jobs.
It is expected that this will attract about 2.5 billion rubles of investments to the city, and more than 600 new jobs will be created.
The list of economic activities in which the "Abaz" Tor will have a special legal regime of business activities, for example, includes crop production, livestock production, food production, soft drinks and clothing.
Already, the Government of the Republic has signed framework agreements for the implementation of 8 investment projects.
It is also planned to reduce the dependence of the territory on the city-forming enterprise "Abakan mine."
In January 2017, the authorities of the region reported that Hakasia fulfilled all the conditions of the Ministry of Economic Development for the creation of Tor.
The authorities of the Orenburg region did the same.
There, the city of Novotroitsk will also create a territory of advanced social and economic development.
This will diversify the economy of the monocity, reduce its dependence on the city-forming enterprise of JSC "Ural Steel," as well as create more than 2.3 thousand jobs and attract investments in the amount of more than 8 million rubles.
The list of economic activities, in which the new Tor will have a special legal regime for entrepreneurs, includes, inter alia, freshwater fish farming, the production of feed, medicines and medical materials.
Novotroitsk became the first of the monocities of the Orenburg region to receive the status of Tor.
Recall that the territory of advanced development is an economic zone with preferential tax conditions, simplified administrative procedures and other privileges, which is created to attract investment and improve the lives of the population.
Among the benefits for Tor residents are: a profit tax of no more than 5% for the first five years, and no less than 10% for the next five years, social contributions of 7.6% for 10 years, the use of a free customs zone, preferential access to various infrastructure, and preferential rent rates.
